  "category_subtitle": "How to say age in Japanese",
 "category_detail": "<b>Counting Age in Japanese (年齢 / ねんれい / nenrei)</b><br><br>In Japanese, age is expressed using the counter <b>歳 (さい / sai)</b>. This counter is attached after a number to indicate how old someone is.<br><br><b>Basic Pattern</b><br>Number + 歳 (さい / sai)<br><br><span class=\"example\">10歳</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(じゅっさい / jussai)</span><br><span class=\"example\">18歳</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(じゅうはっさい / juuhassai)</span><br><span class=\"example\">25歳</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(にじゅうごさい / nijuu gosai)</span><br><br><b>Sound Changes</b><br>Some numbers change pronunciation when combined with 歳.<br><br><span class=\"example\">1歳</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(いっさい / issai)</span><br><span class=\"example\">8歳</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(はっさい / hassai)</span><br><span class=\"example\">10歳</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(じゅっさい / jussai)</span><br><br><b>Special Exception</b><br><span class=\"example\">20歳</span> <span class=\"romaji\">(はたち / hatachi)</span><br>This is a completely special reading and does not follow the normal number + 歳 pattern.<br><br><b>Example Sentences</b><br><span class=\"example\">私は二十歳です。</span><br><span class=\"romaji\">Watashi wa hatachi desu.</span><br><span class=\"meaning\">I am 20 years old.</span><br><br><span class=\"example\">彼は十八歳です。</span><br><span class=\"romaji\">Kare wa juuhassai desu.</span><br><span class=\"meaning\">He is 18 years old.</span>",
